Privacy Policy for Periodly
Last Updated: January 1, 2026
1. Introduction
Welcome to Periodly ("we," "our," or "us"). Periodly is a period tracking application designed to help you monitor your menstrual cycle, track symptoms, and receive predictions about your cycle phases.
This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use Periodly. By using our application, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
2. Information We Collect
2.1 Data You Provide
Periodly collects the following information that you voluntarily enter:
Menstrual cycle dates (start and end dates)
Symptom data (mood, energy levels, pain intensity, bleeding intensity)
Personal notes and observations
Cycle length preferences and settings
Reminder preferences
2.2 Automatically Collected Information
Device information (iOS version, device model)
App usage statistics (for crash reporting and performance improvement)
No personal identifiers are collected automatically
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information you provide solely to:
Provide period tracking and prediction features
Generate cycle statistics and analytics
Send you reminders based on your preferences
Improve app performance and fix bugs
4. Data Storage and Privacy
4.1 Local Storage
All your personal health data is stored exclusively on your device. We do not transmit, sync, or store your cycle data on external servers. Your information remains private and under your control.
4.2 No Cloud Sync
Periodly does not use cloud storage or synchronization services. All data is stored locally using Core Data on your iOS device.
4.3 Data Security
While we implement security measures to protect your data, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your device.
5. Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties. Your cycle data is never shared with:
Advertisers
Analytics companies
Health insurance companies
Other apps or services
Any external parties
6. Third-Party Services
Periodly may use third-party services for:
Crash reporting and analytics (anonymized data only)
App Store distribution
These services may collect anonymized, non-personal information in accordance with their own privacy policies.
7. Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access your data at any time through the app
Delete your data by uninstalling the app or using in-app deletion features
Export your data (feature may be available in future updates)
Stop using the app at any time
8. Children's Privacy
Periodly is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
10. Important Disclaimer and Limitation of Liability
10.1 Medical Disclaimer
PERIODLY IS A TRACKING APPLICATION ONLY AND IS NOT INTENDED FOR MEDICAL USE.
Periodly is designed solely as a personal tracking tool to help you monitor your menstrual cycle. This application:
Is NOT a medical device
Does NOT provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment
Does NOT replace professional medical consultation
Should NOT be used as the sole basis for medical decisions
10.2 No Medical Guarantees
The predictions, statistics, and information provided by Periodly are based on algorithms and user-input data. We make no guarantees regarding:
Accuracy of cycle predictions
Reliability of ovulation forecasts
Effectiveness for pregnancy planning
Suitability for any medical purpose
10.3 Limitation of Liability
TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUES, WHETHER INCURRED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, RESULTING FROM:
Your use or inability to use Periodly
Any errors, mistakes, or inaccuracies in the app's predictions or data
Any decisions made based on information provided by Periodly
Any health-related consequences arising from use of the app
Pregnancy, contraception, or fertility-related outcomes
Any failure to track or predict menstrual cycles accurately
Loss or corruption of your data
Any unauthorized access to or use of your data
10.4 No Warranty
Periodly is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied, including but not limited to:
Warranties of merchantability
Fitness for a particular purpose
Accuracy or reliability of predictions
Non-infringement of third-party rights
10.5 User Responsibility
YOU ARE SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR:
The accuracy of data you enter into Periodly
Any medical or health decisions you make
Consulting with healthcare professionals for medical advice
Using the app in accordance with this Privacy Policy and Terms of Use
Backing up your data if desired
10.6 Not for Emergency Use
Periodly should NEVER be used in emergency situations or for urgent medical needs. Always seek immediate professional medical attention for health emergencies.
11. Use at Your Own Risk
YOU ACKNOWLEDGE AND AGREE THAT YOUR USE OF PERIODLY IS AT YOUR SOLE RISK. We are not responsible for any consequences, health-related or otherwise, that may result from your use of this application. Periodly is a simple tracking tool and should be used as such.
12. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:
Email: support@periodly.app
Website: https://periodly.app
13. Consent
By using Periodly, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Use. If you do not agree with any part of this policy, please do not use Periodly.
Summary: Periodly is a simple period tracking application. All your data is stored locally on your device. We are not responsible for any consequences resulting from the use of this app. This is a tracking tool only, not a medical device. Use at your own risk and always consult healthcare professionals for medical advice.
